DocTemplateDefinition.Name: Image Texture
DocTemplateDefinition.Documentation:
Image textures are based on external files in common image formats such as PNG or JPEG. Such files may be located on servers according to absolute URLs, on the same server as the IFC file according to relative URLs, within the same local directory according to relative file path, within an IFC-ZIP file according to relative file path, or within an arbitrary directory according to absolute file path.
Absolute URLs are recommended for textures published at a location deemed to be permanent (independent of the building model data), while relative URLs are recommended for all other sharing scenarios. Local file paths should be avoided.
Scaling is supported to correlate the size of a texture with its physical dimensions, and enables usage of textures on parametric geometry such that texture coordinates need not be defined.

DocTemplateDefinition.Name: Geometry
DocTemplateDefinition.Documentation: Geometric items are used to describe shape representations of products.

DocTemplateDefinition.Name: CompositeCurve Profile Definition
DocTemplateDefinition.Documentation: Composite curve profile definitons define the closed two-dimensional curve used for the cross-section by a composite curve, consisting of multiple composite curve segments. Each composite curve segment has a parent curve, being either a polyline or a trimmed curve. Trimmed curves have basis curves of type line, circle or ellipse.

DocTemplateDefinition.Name: PolyCurve Profile Definition
DocTemplateDefinition.Documentation:
Poly curve profile definitons define the closed two-dimensional curve used for the cross-section by a indexed poly curve having straight and circular arc segments.
> NOTE  The indexed poly curve has been introduced to provide a less complex and less data set size consuming definition compared to the composite curve.

DocTemplateDefinition.Name: PolyCurve with Voids Profile Definition
DocTemplateDefinition.Documentation:
Poly curve profile definitons define the closed two-dimensional curve used for the cross-section by a indexed poly curve having straight and circular arc segments.
> NOTE  The indexed poly curve has been introduced to provide a less complex and less data set size consuming definition compared to the composite curve.

DocTemplateDefinition.Name: Layer
DocTemplateDefinition.Documentation: Presentation layers may be used to organize geometry into groups that may be shown or hidden. Such designation is only for viewing and editing purposes and does not imply any semantic meaning.

DocTemplateDefinition.Name: Material Properties
DocTemplateDefinition.Documentation: Material properties may capture standard or user-defined parameters.

DocTemplateDefinition.Name: Profile Definition
DocTemplateDefinition.Documentation: Profiles are used to describe cross-sections of swept solid geometry.

DocTemplateDefinition.Name: Arbitrary Profile Definition
DocTemplateDefinition.Documentation: Arbitrary profile defintions are used to describe cross-sections of swept solid geometry using curve segments defined by closed two-dimensional curves.

DocTemplateDefinition.Name: Profile Properties
DocTemplateDefinition.Documentation: Profile properties may capture standard or user-defined parameters.

DocTemplateDefinition.Name: Texture
DocTemplateDefinition.Documentation: Texturing allows for realistic visualization of geometry, such that elements may be more easily and efficiently recognized, and construction details may be specifically indicated.

DocTemplateDefinition.Name: Values
DocTemplateDefinition.Documentation: Properties may contain user-defined data, where data types are open-ended.
